<p>All, Forgive me I am just newbie for CruiseControl.net. After read some tutorial about how to get start with it . I found actually it is important to understand what can be allowed to write in the <code>ccnet.config</code> file. and How it is works.</p>  <p>So I tried to figure out what is inside the <code>ccnet.xsd</code> and <code>CCNetConfigBuilder.xsd</code>.  Here it is .I just show it in the xmlspy 2010.</p>  <p><a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/c2UZQ.png" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/c2UZQ.png" alt="enter image description here"></a></p>  <p><a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/WPiM8.png" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/WPiM8.png" alt="enter image description here"></a></p>  <p>From the schema of cc.net. In my understanding. The root element of configuration is <code>cruisecontrol</code>.  and the sub elements of it could be <code>project</code>, <code>queue</code>, <code>cb:define</code> or <code>cb:scope</code>. these elements can be Occurs times from "0"  to "unbounded".</p>  <p>But When I looked at the examples of ccnet.config from <a href="http://www.cruisecontrolnet.org/projects/ccnet/wiki/Step_2_Build_on_Check-in" rel="nofollow">http://www.cruisecontrolnet.org/projects/ccnet/wiki/Step_2_Build_on_Check-in</a></p>  <p>For example: </p>  <pre><code>&lt;cb:scope ProjectName="ProjectX"&gt;   &lt;cb:define ProjectType="_CI" /&gt;   &lt;project name="$(ProjectName)$(ProjectType)" queue="Q1" queuePriority="901"&gt;      .....   &lt;/project&gt; &lt;/cb:scope&gt; </code></pre>  <p>What makes me confused is:</p>  <p>Why the <code>cb:scope</code> can be the father node of <code>project</code>? Because I didn't see this parent and child relationship is defined in the cc.net xsd.( Please correct me if I am wrong.)? </p>